esolves its runtime dependencies directly, and meaningful core coverage can use built-in MapPropertySource, PropsPropertySource, system properties, environment-variable maps, decoders, preprocessors, and validators without adding parser modules, Docker, or external services.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Keep tests core-only. Use built-in properties/MapPropertySource or injected EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource/SystemPropertiesPropertySource maps. If using real System.setProperty values, set and clear them inside the test. Avoid YAML/JSON/TOML/HOCON examples unless the matching hoplite-* parser module is intentionally added by the test author.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The documentation's common YAML/JSON-style examples require optional hoplite parser modules, but Java .props and in-memory property sources are built into hoplite-core.\",\n    \"Upstream hoplite-core tests use Testcontainers/PostgreSQL for one JdbcHostnameValidator path, but the validator only checks InetAddress reachability, so meaningful coverage can avoid Docker by using loopback/localhost or by testing failure paths.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_084ded2719ae8dee016a3f0ea8098c819584098eb16fbaa033\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2416, "output": 778, "cacheRead": 36864, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40058, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782517405640, "responseId": "resp_084ded2719ae8dee016a3f0e9e47788195805d7d40fc1a5aa7"}}
